{
  "texts": [
    "The realm of cybersecurity is fraught with various types of attacks employed by cybercriminals, hackers, and other digital adversaries.",
    "Their primary objective is to gain unauthorized access to computer networks or systems, often with the intention of altering, destroying, or exposing sensitive information.",
    "These cyberattacks can target individuals, enterprises, or even governmental entities.",
    "According to the \"2021 SonicWall Cyber Threat Report,\" there has been a significant 62% increase in global ransomware attacks in 2020, with over 304 million reported incidents.",
    "This surge in attacks has underscored the urgent need for more robust cybersecurity measures, leading to the development of innovative techniques such as Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) algorithms."
  ]
}